{
  "doc_id": "29686",
  "text": "Tie2 is classified as a receptor tyrosine kinase [CITATION_1] and, when occupied by Ang-1, it activates a series of signaling cascades, including the phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) and Akt cascades. PI3K has also been reported to be involved in the regulation of angiogenesis. For example, PI3K inhibition impaired retinal angiogenesis in zebrafish [CITATION_2] and EC-specific PTEN knockout increased retinal vascular development [CITATION_3] .",
